    <div class="field field-name-field-image field-type-image field-label-hidden"><a href="http://timonweb.com/fixing-views-scroll-to-top-when-you-have-a-fixed-header"><img typeof="foaf:Image" src="http://timonweb.com/sites/default/files/styles/post-images/public/post-images/scroll-to-top.png?itok=4lW2RP1X" width="150" height="150" alt="" /></a></div><div class="field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden"><p>Drupal Views offers us a cool feature: ajaxified pagers. When you click on a pager, it changes the page without reloading the main page itself and then scrolls to the top of the view. It works great, but sometimes you may encounter a problem: if you have a fixed header on your page (the one that stays on top when you scroll the page) it will overlap with the top of your view container thus scroll to top won't work preciselly correct and the header will cover the top part of your view.</p></div><div class="field field-name-taxonomy-vocabulary-1 field-type-taxonomy-term-reference field-label-hidden">
